Poems:
(that is, the plot of land)
where the fish are conveyed,
as rivers of ripened wood;
where the handle of a fork is cut into the
nuances of string;
where the pastures are closed with tulips,
and forests of oak branches;
where the woodpecker lives on the hillside,
as the keeper watches for her

I don’t know if I am mad or sad or if 
I am never mad, as there is always somewhere 
right where the road goes, wrong place, wrong time.

 It’s like saying:
Just get out of here, young man, get out of here;
this is the right place and only;


And here is what happens: the mind’s an almost vapid mound of rubble and sand;
nothing moves, all seems dissolved in its own translucent aether;


Again and again and again the voice inside me has sounded
a strange amen, like coming to terms with what we have
suffered and that loss does not, let us say

Up through their corsages. Up through their skirts;

Under their soft furriers. O nation’s head;

Amidst their ships' tails;
The wind swept them
back and forth into the night.
O city. O dear city. 


 How people describe this scene

It’s in the language of animals
